Our Reporter  In online music platform, Next Media TV, has been launched recently. Built by Carel Studios, Lagos, the platform, a 24-hour online gospel music television had over 100,000 viewers on its first day of broadcast. It was gathered that the platform was created to propagate and disseminate the gospel of Jesus Christ.  Presently, Next Music TV has about a million viewers from across 20 countries and a daily viewership of over 80,000 people live-streaming new releases, trending videos and musical concerts from different artistes. ”Once you subscribe, you will get notifications on programmes like ‘The Hits’, ‘Art of Praise’, ‘Light up with music’, ‘Gospel turn up’, and ‘Just Gospel,’” a source stated. “It also gives you first-hand information on new and upcoming gospel music.”